OL,3,CWorkers to be given twice as long to
OL,4,Cstrike under Government proposals
OL,6,FWorkers would be given twice as long
OL,7,Fto strike under proposals being
OL,8,Fconsidered by the Government.
OL,10,FUnions could be able to stage walkouts
OL,11,Ffor up to a year after balloting
OL,12,Fmembers, according to a consultation
OL,13,Fdocument produced by the Department
OL,14,Ffor Business and Trade.
OL,16,FUnder existing legislation, if workers
OL,17,Fvote to strike, the mandate expires
OL,18,Fafter six months and another poll must
OL,19,Fbe carried out for any following
OL,20,Faction to be valid.
