OL,3,CWorkers to be given twice as long to
OL,4,Cstrike under Government proposals
OL,6,FThe Government said doubling this time
OL,7,Fperiod would "strike the correct
OL,8,Fbalance" between ensuring action is
OL,9,Fbased on a recent vote and reducing
OL,10,Fthe need for "costly and time-
OL,11,Fconsuming" re-ballots.
OL,13,FThe proposed measures are part of a
OL,14,Fmajor overhaul of workers' rights
OL,15,Foverseen by Deputy Prime Minister
OL,16,FAngela Rayner and Business Secretary
OL,17,FJonathan Reynolds.
