OL,3,CWorkers to be given twice as long to
OL,4,Cstrike under Government proposals
OL,6,FExisting rules mean that 10% of a
OL,7,Fworkforce must be union members for an
OL,8,Fapplication to be made to get
OL,9,Frecognition to negotiate with
OL,10,Femployers, but ministers are planning
OL,11,Fto lower this to 2%.
OL,13,FThe Government is also considering
OL,14,Frelaxing requirements on unions to
OL,15,Fshow that they have repudiated so-
OL,16,Fcalled "wildcat" strikes by workers
OL,17,Fwhich they have not authorised or
OL,18,Forganised.
