OL,3,CWorkers to be given twice as long to
OL,4,Cstrike under Government proposals
OL,6,FA general notice posted online and
OL,7,Fnotifying the officials and employers
OL,8,Finvolved could be enough to show it
OL,9,Fdoes not support the action, rather
OL,10,Fthan the present requirement to give
OL,11,Findividual written notice to all staff
OL,12,Fbelieved to be taking part, the
OL,13,Fconsultation document suggests.
OL,15,FThey said that under the
OL,16,FConservatives, "strikes did not happen
OL,17,Fbecause workers or trade unions had
OL,18,Ftoo much power" but because "ministers
OL,19,Fchose to avoid grown-up negotiation."
